"use strict";(self.webpackChunkdocumentation=self.webpackChunkdocumentation||[]).push([[3049],{6323:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"change-of-architecture","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/change-of-architecture","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-25-change-of-architecture.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-25-change-of-architecture.md","title":"Change of architecture \ud83c\udfd7\ufe0f","description":"I made a major update! The architecture of my system changed \ud83d\ude80 from monolithic synchronous to microservice parallel.","date":"2025-08-25T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Story","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/story","description":"Talking about something"}],"readingTime":0.49,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"change-of-architecture","title":"Change of architecture \ud83c\udfd7\ufe0f","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["story"]},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"\ud83c\udf00 The Query Language Has Radically Changed","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/metamorphosis-dsl"}},"content":"**I made a major update!** The architecture of my system **changed** \ud83d\ude80 from monolithic synchronous to microservice parallel.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n## Pros of the changes \u2705\\n\\n1) **The architecture became clearer**: there is no one big \\"black box\\". \ud83d\udc4f\\n2) **The system became faster**: processing time decreased from ~60 seconds to ~20 seconds. \u26a1\\n3) **The quality of responses remained the same** - the amount of tasks performed remained the same. \ud83c\udfaf\\n\\n## Cons of the changes \u26a0\ufe0f\\n\\n**The cost of development increased** due to the complexity of the distributed system. \ud83d\udcb8\\n\\n**Overall, the switch was worth it** \ud83c\udf1f - the over 60% performance improvement is worth the extra development effort."},{"id":"metamorphosis-dsl","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/metamorphosis-dsl","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-21-metamorphosis-dsl.mdx","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-21-metamorphosis-dsl.mdx","title":"\ud83c\udf00 The Query Language Has Radically Changed","description":"Recently, my DSL has undergone several changes: it was renamed, its syntax was modified, and eventually it disappeared entirely.","date":"2025-08-21T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Story","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/story","description":"Talking about something"},{"inline":false,"label":"Idea","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/idea","description":"Ideas for the project"}],"readingTime":1.11,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"metamorphosis-dsl","title":"\ud83c\udf00 The Query Language Has Radically Changed","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["story","idea"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Change of architecture \ud83c\udfd7\ufe0f","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/change-of-architecture"},"nextItem":{"title":"Database Migration from Markdown to YAML","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/DB-to-yaml"}},"content":"Recently, my [DSL](/blog/about-my-dsl) has undergone several changes: it was renamed, its syntax was modified, and eventually it disappeared entirely.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n:::info \ud83d\udd04 Name Change\\n[After the latest updates](/blog/yql), the DSL was renamed to:\\n\\n**NorQL** - *Norchevsky Query Language*\\n\\nThis ensures the name is associated with the project rather than just a file format.\\n:::\\n\\nBut yesterday, the DSL was completely retired, unable to compete with the new concept of agent-database interaction.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcda NFL - Norchevsky\'s Functional Library\\nInstead of a full DSL, there will now be a library of functions that agents can call.\\n\\nThese functions are similar to tools from the Python LangChain library.\\n\\nThe functions are divided into 3 categories:\\n\\nimport Tabs from \'@theme/Tabs\';\\nimport TabItem from \'@theme/TabItem\';\\n\\n<Tabs>\\n  <TabItem value=\\"1\\" label=\\"Low-Level\\" default>\\n    Provide direct access to database files.\\n    :::note For example\\n    - Retrieving subsections\\n    - Reading section text\\n    - Updating/adding text or sections\\n    :::\\n    Direct work with YAML files.\\n  </TabItem>\\n  <TabItem value=\\"2\\" label=\\"High-Level\\">\\n    Work with multiple YAML files:\\n    - Data filtering\\n    - Querying specific data (e.g., schemas of multiple files)\\n  </TabItem>\\n  <TabItem value=\\"3\\" label=\\"\ud83d\ude80 Hyper-Functions\\">\\n    Combine the functionality of multiple high-level functions.\\n    :::note Advantage\\n    Instead of creating multiple functions with unique names and arguments, a single function was developed that can perform their tasks when provided with appropriate arguments.\\n    :::\\n  </TabItem>\\n</Tabs>"},{"id":"DB-to-yaml","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/DB-to-yaml","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-14-DATABASE-to-yaml-translation.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-14-DATABASE-to-yaml-translation.md","title":"Database Migration from Markdown to YAML","description":"Due to the convenience of YAML, the database was migrated from Markdown.","date":"2025-08-14T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Idea","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/idea","description":"Ideas for the project"}],"readingTime":0.88,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"DB-to-yaml","title":"Database Migration from Markdown to YAML","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["idea"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"\ud83c\udf00 The Query Language Has Radically Changed","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/metamorphosis-dsl"},"nextItem":{"title":"About My Query Language \ud83d\udcac","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/about-my-dsl"}},"content":"Due to the convenience of YAML, the database was migrated from Markdown.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Why Did We Switch to YAML? \ud83e\udd14\\n\\nPreviously, our database used the Markdown (`.md`) format. While Markdown is excellent for human readability, its machine processing was challenging:\\n\\n- **AST Transformations** \ud83d\udd04:  \\n  Any data modification required:\\n  1. Parsing MD into an Abstract Syntax Tree (AST)\\n  2. Making changes to the AST\\n  3. Converting back to MD\\n- **Fragility** \u26a0\ufe0f:  \\n  Slight markup deviations could break the parser\\n- **Limited Structure** \ud83d\udce6:  \\n  Difficult to express nested data relationships\\n\\n## Advantages of YAML \ud83d\ude80\\n\\nThe transition to YAML solved these problems:\\n\\n```yaml\\n# Example data structure in YAML\\ncharacter:\\n  id: hero_ivan\\n  name: Ivan\\n  stats:\\n    strength: 15\\n    agility: 12\\n  inventory:\\n    - sword\\n    - health_potion\\n```\\n\\n- **Direct Parsing** \u26a1:  \\n  Data is immediately available as structured objects (lists, dictionaries)\\n- **Readability** \ud83d\udc41\ufe0f:  \\n  Data hierarchy is visually obvious\\n- **Change Safety** \ud83d\udd12:  \\n  Modify only specific fields without full re-parsing\\n- **Metadata Support** \ud83c\udff7\ufe0f:  \\n  Easy to add tags, comments, and data types\\n\\n### Final Gains \u23f1\ufe0f\ud83d\udcbe\\n- Data processing speed increased by 3x\\n- Database handling code simplified by 40%\\n- Parsing errors: 0\ufe0f\u20e3\\n\\nNow we can focus on game logic development instead of fighting formats! \ud83c\udfae\u2728"},{"id":"about-my-dsl","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/about-my-dsl","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-14-about-my-dsl.mdx","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-14-about-my-dsl.mdx","title":"About My Query Language \ud83d\udcac","description":"I\'ve rethought the idea of my language several times \u2014 and it has changed radically! \ud83d\udd04","date":"2025-08-14T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Story","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/story","description":"Talking about something"}],"readingTime":1.59,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"about-my-dsl","title":"About My Query Language \ud83d\udcac","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["story"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Database Migration from Markdown to YAML","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/DB-to-yaml"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rebranding MQL to YQL \ud83c\udfa8","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/yql"}},"content":"I\'ve rethought the idea of [my language](/blog/MDQL) several times \u2014 and it has changed radically! \ud83d\udd04\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## History of My DSL: From MDQL to MQL\\n\\nimport Tabs from \'@theme/Tabs\';\\nimport TabItem from \'@theme/TabItem\';\\n\\n<Tabs>\\n  <TabItem value=\\"similar\\" label=\\"Similar to GraphQL\\" default>\\n    This version is described in [this blog post](/blog/MDQL) and has similarities to GraphQL \ud83d\udc65\\n  </TabItem>\\n  <TabItem value=\\"rethinking\\" label=\\"Syntax Change\\">\\n    Changed GraphQL syntax to JSON for its universality \ud83d\udce6\\n    Here\'s what it looked like (approximately):\\n    ```json\\n    {\\n        \\"meta\\": {\\n            \\"request_goal\\": \\"Get character data\\",\\n            \\"agent_name\\": \\"Gemini\\",\\n            \\"request_method\\": \\"select\\"\\n        },\\n        \\"query_block\\": {\\n            \\"file_path\\": {\\n                \\"folder_name\\": \\"Characters\\",\\n                \\"file_name\\": \\"Kowalski, the bloody reaper\\"\\n            },\\n            \\"sections_to_retrieve\\": [\\n                {\\n                    \\"YAML\\": {\\n                        \\"name\\": \\"get_text\\"\\n                    }\\n                },\\n                {\\n                    \\"Bio\\": {\\n                        \\"Character\\": \\"get_text\\"\\n                    }\\n                },\\n                {\\n                    \\"Abilities\\": {\\n                        \\"list_elements\\": [1, 3]\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            ]\\n        }\\n    }\\n    ```\\n  </TabItem>\\n  <TabItem value=\\"rethinking2\\" label=\\"Syntax Change 2\\">\\n    Changed JSON syntax to YAML for a more concise look: it\'s less bulky while maintaining functionality \u2728\\n    Here\'s what it looked like (approximately):\\n    ```yaml\\n    meta:\\n        request_goal: Get character data\\n        agent_name: Gemini\\n        request_method: select\\n    \\n    query_block:\\n        file_path:\\n            folder_name: Characters\\n            file_name: Kowalski, the bloody reaper\\n        \\n        sections_to_retrieve:\\n            - YAML:\\n                name: get_text\\n            - Bio:\\n                Character: get_text\\n            - Abilities:\\n                list_elements: [1, 3]\\n    ```\\n  </TabItem>\\n  <TabItem value=\\"return\\" label=\\"Complete Replacement \ud83d\ude80\\">\\n    From something vaguely resembling GraphQL (if you squint hard \ud83d\ude48) I came to SQL.\\n    :::info What it was before\\n    The agent specified the full path to the required location, from the root to the text in some nested heading.\\n    :::\\n    Now it\'s a maximally SQL-like syntax: instead of specifying paths, simply listing headings to extract text from.\\n\\n    Simply put, the schema was simplified to the minimum and now matches the key idea of the project \u2705\\n    \\n    Here\'s what it looks like now:\\n    ```sql\\n    -- Get text from two character sections \ud83d\udc64\\n    SELECT text\\n    FROM \\"\u041e\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435\\", \\"\u0418\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u044f\\"\\n    FILE \\"\u041f\u0435\u0440\u0441\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0436\u0438/character\\";\\n    \\n    -- Get first 3 events with fields \ud83d\udcc5\\n    SELECT title, tags, text\\n    FROM \\"\u0421\u043e\u0431\u044b\u0442\u0438\u044f\\"\\n    FILE \\"\u0421\u043e\u0431\u044b\u0442\u0438\u044f/events\\"\\n    LIMIT 3;\\n    \\n    -- Get items with \\"\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0432\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\\" tag and hunger state \ud83e\udd85\\n    SELECT items\\n    FROM \\"\u0421\u043e\u0431\u044b\u0442\u0438\u044f\\"\\n    FILE \\"\u0421\u043e\u0431\u044b\u0442\u0438\u044f/events\\"\\n    WHERE tags INCLUDE \\"\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0432\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\\"\\n      AND state INCLUDE \\"\u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0434 > 50\\";\\n    ```\\n  </TabItem>\\n</Tabs>"},{"id":"yql","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/yql","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-14-yql.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-14-yql.md","title":"Rebranding MQL to YQL \ud83c\udfa8","description":"Due to the database migration to YAML, the query language was renamed:","date":"2025-08-14T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Story","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/story","description":"Talking about something"}],"readingTime":0.12,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"yql","title":"Rebranding MQL to YQL \ud83c\udfa8","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["story"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"About My Query Language \ud83d\udcac","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/about-my-dsl"},"nextItem":{"title":"About the Complexity of the Project","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/about-the-complexity-of-the-project"}},"content":"Due to the [database migration to YAML](/blog/db-to-yaml), the query language was renamed: \\nMQL (Markdown Query Language) \u2192 YQL (YAML Query Language) \ud83d\udd04\ud83d\ude80"},{"id":"about-the-complexity-of-the-project","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/about-the-complexity-of-the-project","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-12-about-the-complexity-of-the-project.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-12-about-the-complexity-of-the-project.md","title":"About the Complexity of the Project","description":"I was thinking about starting to develop an MVP, dug a little into the episode memory and... \ud83d\ude05","date":"2025-08-12T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Story","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/story","description":"Talking about something"}],"readingTime":0.54,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"about-the-complexity-of-the-project","title":"About the Complexity of the Project","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["story"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rebranding MQL to YQL \ud83c\udfa8","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/yql"},"nextItem":{"title":"Replacement of the main page","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/replacement-of-the-main-page"}},"content":"I was thinking about starting to develop an MVP, dug a little into the episode memory and... \ud83d\ude05\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Simply Speaking \ud83e\udd14\\nI started thinking about which components to add to the MVP, and thought about episodic memory. Seems like nothing heavy:\\n- Integrate a BYaM agent response verification pipeline for reminders\\n- Create a small database for storing episodes\\n- And the md file scheme doesn\'t seem heavy\\n\\nThen a bunch of fundamental questions poured in: \ud83e\udd2f\\n- What is an episode?\\n- How does it start and end?\\n- How will the [hooks system](/hooks-and-paths) work?\\n- And so on.\\n\\n## So the project is so heavy that a whole new module arose from nowhere \ud83d\ude32"},{"id":"replacement-of-the-main-page","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/replacement-of-the-main-page","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-10-replacement-of-the-main-page.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-10-replacement-of-the-main-page.md","title":"Replacement of the main page","description":"I changed the main page to the former one, simply because I didn\'t like the old main page","date":"2025-08-10T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Story","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/story","description":"Talking about something"}],"readingTime":0.09,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"replacement-of-the-main-page","title":"Replacement of the main page","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["story"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"About the Complexity of the Project","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/about-the-complexity-of-the-project"},"nextItem":{"title":"Added a scheme for Norchevsky","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/added-norchevsky-scheme"}},"content":"I changed the main page to the former one, simply because I didn\'t like the old main page"},{"id":"added-norchevsky-scheme","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/added-norchevsky-scheme","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-09-added-norchevsky-scheme.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-09-added-norchevsky-scheme.md","title":"Added a scheme for Norchevsky","description":"Added the promised scheme of Norchevsky\'s work to the welcome page.","date":"2025-08-09T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Story","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/story","description":"Talking about something"}],"readingTime":0.06,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"added-norchevsky-scheme","title":"Added a scheme for Norchevsky","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["story"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Replacement of the main page","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/replacement-of-the-main-page"},"nextItem":{"title":"Battle Module","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/battle-module"}},"content":"Added the promised scheme of Norchevsky\'s work to the welcome page."},{"id":"battle-module","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/battle-module","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-09-battle-module.mdx","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-09-battle-module.mdx","title":"Battle Module","description":"I came up with a battle module for Norchevsky","date":"2025-08-09T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Idea","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/idea","description":"Ideas for the project"}],"readingTime":1.17,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"battle-module","title":"Battle Module","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["idea"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Added a scheme for Norchevsky","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/added-norchevsky-scheme"},"nextItem":{"title":"Failure in Localization \ud83d\ude1e","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/failure-in-localization"}},"content":"I came up with a battle module for Norchevsky\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n:::note Key Features?\\n- Positioning in space and time of all objects \\n_(characters, items, covers, etc.)_\\n- Tracking and aggregation of all objects\' state\\n- Convenient access to tracking data\\n- Conducting the battle itself\\n:::\\n\\n## Battle Management Ideas\\n\\nimport Tabs from \'@theme/Tabs\';\\nimport TabItem from \'@theme/TabItem\';\\n\\n<Tabs>\\n  <TabItem value=\\"round dance\\" label=\\"Round Dance\\" default>\\n    There is one main _agent_ that programmatically calculates all possible decisions and, based on this data and orders from above, determines the behavior of battle participants.\\n    :::info Pros\\n    Good dynamics due to comprehensive non-player combat design\\n    :::\\n\\n    :::danger Cons\\n    - Hyper-factorial complexity\\n    - Too many calculations required\\n    - Risk of the round dance agent being overwhelmed by data\\n    :::\\n  </TabItem>\\n  <TabItem value=\\"swarm\\" label=\\"Swarm\\">\\n    Each battle participant has their own agent (and AI), their own memory, and is fully autonomous. The battle is conducted in turn-based mode.\\n    :::info Pros\\n    - Easier to implement due to turn-based system and local processing\\n    - Can create more scenarios (e.g., when an agent fails to notice something)\\n    :::\\n\\n    :::warning Cons\\n    Slightly reduced dynamics, but since AI processes quickly, turns will be returned to the player promptly.\\n    :::\\n  </TabItem>\\n  <TabItem value=\\"hybrid\\" label=\\"Hybrid\\">\\n    A blend of both previous approaches, attempting to combine their strengths.\\n    \\n    Differs from the swarm by having a central coordinator that reminds agents of common goals, tactics, and other pre-agreed battle parameters.\\n  </TabItem>\\n</Tabs>"},{"id":"failure-in-localization","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/failure-in-localization","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-09-failure-in-localization.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-09-failure-in-localization.md","title":"Failure in Localization \ud83d\ude1e","description":"I tried, but I couldn\'t get the localization to work. \ud83d\ude13","date":"2025-08-09T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Story","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/story","description":"Talking about something"}],"readingTime":0.18,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"failure-in-localization","title":"Failure in Localization \ud83d\ude1e","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["story"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Battle Module","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/battle-module"},"nextItem":{"title":"Your own structured query language","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/MDQL"}},"content":"I tried, but I couldn\'t get the localization to work. \ud83d\ude13\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\nI spent the whole day trying to add an English translation, but no matter what I did or how hard I tried - nothing worked. \ud83d\ude29"},{"id":"MDQL","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/MDQL","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-08-MDQL.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-08-MDQL.md","title":"Your own structured query language","description":"MDQL \u2014 MarkDown Query Language","date":"2025-08-08T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Story","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/story","description":"Talking about something"}],"readingTime":0.91,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"MDQL","title":"Your own structured query language","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["story"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Failure in Localization \ud83d\ude1e","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/failure-in-localization"},"nextItem":{"title":"About Hooks","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/hooks-and-paths"}},"content":"MDQL \u2014 MarkDown Query Language\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\nIf earlier to get context from a file it was necessary to either look at pre-created tl;dr, or ask a separate agent to compress the context from the file,\\n\\nnow there is a separate query language for querying or changing data in MD files \u2014 **MDQL**.\\n\\n:::info MDQL\\nThis is a language inherited from GraphQL, allowing agents to get and change only the necessary data from Markdown files. This ensures programmatic tl;dr, as well as transparency and control over queries.\\n\\nMDQL optimizes work with a large number of documents, reducing data redundancy and speeding up query processing.\\n\\nBoth reading and writing are supported, which allows not only to retrieve information, but also to automatically update or structure the content.\\n\\n__Example__ of a simple MDQL query:\\n\\n```GraphQL\\n{\\n  file(path: \\"characters/hero.md\\") {\\n    frontmatter {\\n      name\\n      role\\n    }\\n    content(filter: \\"skills\\") {\\n      title\\n      description\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n````\\n\\nThis query will extract only the name, role, and description of skills from the hero file.\\n\\n:::caution This is just an example\\nMDQL is just an idea for now, the implementation will most likely look completely different\\n:::"},{"id":"hooks-and-paths","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/hooks-and-paths","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-08-hooks-and-paths.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-08-hooks-and-paths.md","title":"About Hooks","description":"Hooks for Agent Story Generation","date":"2025-08-08T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Idea","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/idea","description":"Ideas for the project"},{"inline":false,"label":"Think","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/think","description":"Thoughts and reflections"}],"readingTime":0.55,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"hooks-and-paths","title":"About Hooks","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["idea","think"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Your own structured query language","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/MDQL"},"nextItem":{"title":"Added a Welcome Page","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/added-welcome-page"}},"content":"Hooks for Agent Story Generation\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n:::info According to the idea, plot hooks are eternal\\n\\nBecause they have connections at different levels:\\n- Primary - the object itself, which has plot possibilities\\n- Secondary - memories/traces of the object\\n:::\\n\\nAnd if so, it turns out that even if an object is lost, it only means that _the system can introduce a plot line_ to find the object, which is good for the game.\\n\\n---\\n\\nOverall, it turns out that the only way to work with hooks is not to use them and add them, because new plot tropes may open up for us, which will create new events that will make more hooks."},{"id":"added-welcome-page","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/added-welcome-page","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-07-added-a-welcome-page.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-07-added-a-welcome-page.md","title":"Added a Welcome Page","description":"First step in the project","date":"2025-08-07T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Story","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/story","description":"Talking about something"}],"readingTime":0.04,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"added-welcome-page","title":"Added a Welcome Page","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["story"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"About Hooks","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/hooks-and-paths"},"nextItem":{"title":"The Idea of Agent Stories","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/the-idea-of-agent-stories"}},"content":"[First](/Norchevsky/welcome) step in the project"},{"id":"the-idea-of-agent-stories","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/the-idea-of-agent-stories","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-07-the-idea-of-agent-stories.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-07-the-idea-of-agent-stories.md","title":"The Idea of Agent Stories","description":"How Agents Invent the Future","date":"2025-08-07T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Idea","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/idea","description":"Ideas for the project"}],"readingTime":0.66,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"the-idea-of-agent-stories","title":"The Idea of Agent Stories","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["idea"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Added a Welcome Page","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/added-welcome-page"},"nextItem":{"title":"Documentation Begins","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/first-blog-post"}},"content":"How Agents Invent the Future\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\nAccording to the idea, worker agents when creating the future must take into account the _present_ and the _past_.\\n\\nThis means they must rely on **their** previous iterations.  \\nThese iterations store not only **what** they did (for example, came up with an event and a way to achieve it),  \\nbut also **what prerequisites** they left for future steps.\\n\\nYes, during generation they can also consider the **context of the whole world**.  \\nTherefore, the formula for generating the future looks something like this:\\n\\n```text\\npast + present + previous iterations + world context = future events\\n```\\n\\n**World context** is everything that agents can additionally introduce into the game while preserving the lore and style,\\nso that something new appears in the story, not just the same thing in a loop."},{"id":"first-blog-post","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/first-blog-post","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-06-first-blog-post.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-06-first-blog-post.md","title":"Documentation Begins","description":"First Steps in Documentation","date":"2025-08-06T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Story","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/story","description":"Talking about something"}],"readingTime":0.13,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"first-blog-post","title":"Documentation Begins","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["story"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"The Idea of Agent Stories","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/the-idea-of-agent-stories"},"nextItem":{"title":"Norchevsky\'s Appearance","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/norchevskys-appearance"}},"content":"First Steps in Documentation\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\nToday is the first day of development! \ud83c\udf89  \\nI chose **Docusaurus** because of:\\n\\n- \u2728 Beauty  \\n- \ud83d\udd27 Versatility\\n\\nIt has blogs, documentation, and separate pages!"},{"id":"norchevskys-appearance","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/norchevskys-appearance","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-05-norchevskys-appearance.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-05-norchevskys-appearance.md","title":"Norchevsky\'s Appearance","description":"The Chthonic Appearance of Norchevsky","date":"2025-08-05T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Think","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/think","description":"Thoughts and reflections"}],"readingTime":0.55,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"norchevskys-appearance","title":"Norchevsky\'s Appearance","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["think"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Documentation Begins","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/first-blog-post"}},"content":"The Chthonic Appearance of Norchevsky\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\nHis true appearance is that of a tall, slender humanoid with a wide mouth stretching from ear to ear filled with sharp teeth, and a single large eye in the middle with a pupil like Dio Brando from JoJo\'s Bizarre Adventure.\\n\\nHe is pitch black, like tar, and his body is covered in some kind of tattered cloth. He is entirely black except for the whites of his eye and his gleaming white teeth.\\n\\nOn his back, there\'s a not very tall but very sharp hump at shoulder blade level.\\n\\nLong, sharp fingers.\\n\\nHe himself is kind-hearted and wouldn\'t hurt a fly.\\n\\n---"}]}}')}}]);